postman blues ( &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ・ &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; ) is a 1997 japanese criminal action comedy-drama film directed and written by hiroyuki tanaka under the name sabu . the film features shin ' ichi tsutsumi , keisuke &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; , ren &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; and kyōko &lt;&lt;unk&gt;&gt; in the lead roles . it tells the story of a postman ( shin ' ichi tsutsumi ) who is mistaken by the police as a criminal . the film was released in japan in 1997 and later in italy in 1999 and brazil in 2003 . hiroyuki tanaka won the new blood award at the 1999 cognac festival du film policier for the film .